The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Fast food chains show appetite for expansion

 KAKOLY CHATTERJEE

 Food for thought

 New Delhi, Aug. 6: Fast food chains such as Dominos Pizza, Nirulas, Pizza Hut and KFC have drawn up expansion plans.

 While Pizza Hut and Kentucky Fried Chicken (KFC) plans to increase the number of outlets from 134 to 175 by the end of this year, Nirulas will add another 25 outlets to its existing 51 by the end of 2008. Dominos Pizza has 140 stores in 31 cities. 

 Sudipta Sengupta, senior vice-president sales and marketing, Nirulas, said, The market is growing by leaps and bounds. The growth is so buoyant that we cannot even project growth rates beyond 2010.

 In the next two to three years, Dominos Pizza plans to open 50 to 60 outlets in 20 more cities. Nirulas is present only in northern India now. It will launch its operations in Mumbai by the first quarter of the next fiscal. 

 It plans to open 50 to 60 outlets in the city. The company will also go to south India by the middle of next year and to the east by 2009. It plans to have 200 outlets by the end of 2009. 

 Pizza Hut and KFC, having explored the metros, will enter Tier I and Tier II markets. 

 Dev Amritesh, vice-presidentmarketing, Dominos Pizza, said, We have a 40 per cent share in the pizza market and our growth last year was a healthy 50 per cent. The quicker we penetrate the Indian market the faster we will grow. 

 As part of its expansion plans, Dominos will also enter the ice cream market. It plans to retail branded ice creams. 

 Nirulas has a production facility in Noida, where it produces 15 thousand litres of ice cream per day. It has two ice cream brands, Nirulas ice cream and Dairy Cream, which is the institutional brand. The company will raise the capacity of its production facility to 20,000 litres a day.

 In the past four years, Dominos Pizza has maintained a steady growth rate of 30 per cent. The growth rate of Nirulas has doubled this year. 

 Niren Chaudhary, managing director of Yum Restaurants, said, During the past two years, Pizza Hut has grown around 10 to 20 per cent. We have experienced a 30 per cent growth in the last two to three months since the new TV commercial went on air.

 We are planning to double our business in the next three years, he added. Pizza Hut and Nirulas are planning to take both equity and franchisee routes for their expansions.




